les durchgegangen: die exakten Akki-Flüche, die gleichen Zutaten samt untragbarem Gestank, dieselben rüden Gesten. Und trotzdem starb niemand._#','#_Oku-Doku aveva ripetuto tutti i movimenti: le stesse maledizioni akki, gli stessi puzzolenti ingredienti, gli stessi gesti volgari. Eppure non era morta una sola persona._#','#_オクドクは、同じ悪忌の呪いの言葉と、同じ悪臭の材料と、同じ下品なしぐさと、あらゆる事柄をやってみた。しかし、誰一人死ぬものはいなかった。_#','#_Oku-Doku tinha executado todos os movimentos: as mesmas maldições dos akkis, os mesmos ingredientes com seu fedor horrendo, os mesmos gestos grosseiros. Mas mesmo assim nenhuma pessoa morreu._#',NULL,'#_Oku-Doku ya se sabía la historia: los mismos insultos akki, los mismos ingredientes apestosos, los mismos gestos vulgares. Sin embargo, no murió ni un alma._#',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),('79223','Stone Rain','CHK','Sorcery','C','{2}{R}','3',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Destroy target land.','#_"The kami struck with gouts of fire, showers of rock, and the combined rage of the spirit world. Only Eiganjo Castle remained standing, glistening untouched in the sun."£—The History of Kamigawa_#',NULL,'Greg Staples','191','4.009',NULL,'R',NULL,'0.09','0.23','1.9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'R','石雨',NULL,'Pluie de pierres','Steinhagel','Pioggia di Pietre','石の雨','Chuva de Pedra',NULL,'Lluvia de piedras',NULL,'法术',NULL,'Rituel','Hexerei','Stregoneria','ソーサリー','Feitiço',NULL,'Conjuro',NULL,'消灭目标地。',NULL,'Détruisez le terrain ciblé.','Zerstöre ein Land deiner Wahl.','Distruggi una terra bersaglio.','土地１つを対象とし、それを破壊する。','Destrói o terreno alvo.',NULL,'Destruye la tierra objetivo.',NULL,'#_「神明降下天火石雨以宣泄灵界之怒；而分毫未损的永岩城依旧屹立不摇，在阳光下闪闪生辉。」～神河通史_#',NULL,'#_« Les kami frappèrent avec des grêles de feu, des pluies de pierres. C''était la colère du monde spirituel qui se déchaînait. Seul le château d''Eiganjo se dressait, imperturbable, baigné des rayons du soleil. » —L''histoire de Kamigawa_#','#_„Die Kami kämpften mit Feuerwellen und Steinhageln, dem vereinten Zorn der Geisterwelt. Nur Burg Eiganjo blieb stehen, unangetastet in der Sonne glänzend." —Die Geschichte von Kamigawa_#','#_"I kami colpirono con getti di fuoco, lancio di pietre e la rabbia congiunta del mondo spirituale. Solo il Castello Eiganjo rimase in piedi, scintillante al sole e perfettamente integro."—La Storia di Kamigawa_#','#_神は、炎の風と、岩の雨と、あらゆる精霊界の怒りで襲い掛かった。唯一永岩城のみがそこに残り、陽を受けて輝いていた。――神河史書_#','#_"Os kamis atacaram com gotas de fogo, chuvas de pedras e com a ira combinada do mundo espiritual. Somente o Castelo Eiganjo permaneceu em pé, cintilando intocado sob o sol".— A História de Kamigawa_#',NULL,'#_"Los kami golpearon con lluvias de fuego y piedras, y la ira combinada del mundo espiritual. Sólo el castillo Eiganjo permaneció en pie, brillando intacto bajo el sol."—La historia de Kamigawa_#',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),('82000','Strange Inversion','CHK','Instant — Arcane','U','{2}{R}','3',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Switch target creature''s power and toughness until end of turn.£Splice onto Arcane {1}{R} #_(As you cast an Arcane spell, you may reveal this card from your hand and pay its splice cost. If you do, add this card''s effects to that spell.)_#',NULL,NULL,'Khang Le','192','2.217','£4/15/2013: Effects that switch power and toughness apply after all other effects that change power and/or toughness, regardless of which effect was created first.£4/15/2013: Switching a creature’s power and toughness twice (or any even number of times) effectively returns the creature to the power and toughness it had before any switches.£6/7/2013: You reveal all cards you intend to splice at the same time. Each individual card can be spliced only once onto any one spell.£6/7/2013: A card with a splice ability can’t be spliced onto itself because the spell is on the stack (and not in your hand) when you reveal the cards you want to splice onto it.£6/7/2013: You choose all targets for the spell after revealing cards you want to splice, including any targets r